🔷 Legal Calculus Is Not AI Output
It is a procedural discipline.

It does not hand over machine judgment.
It teaches people how to build, test, and refine legal thought.

At its core:

🟦 Architect AI organizes
🟩 Builder AI expands
🟨 Inspector AI challenges
🟧 Human Strategist decides

That last role is the key.

AI does not decide the theory of the case.
AI does not choose controlling facts.
AI does not weigh credibility.
AI does not replace judgment.

The human does.

Legal Calculus is not automation.
It is iterative, human-directed procedural work.

AI drafts.
AI checks.
AI proposes.
The human Strategist interprets, selects, corrects, and signs.

That is why Legal Calculus remains:

🟦 educational
🟩 procedural
🟨 judgment-centered
🟧 human-accountable

Bottom line:
Legal Calculus is not AI autonomy.
It is human judgment using disciplined tools.